  <header class="main-hd">
    <h3 class="title">
      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/1040880/" class="title-link">《花间一壶酒》读后</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-1040880"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/1069594/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img1.doubanio.com/icon/user_normal.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/1069594/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">李浔阳</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar40 main-title-rating" title="推荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2006-04-27"
      class="main-meta">2006-04-27 12:09:05</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_1040880_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                   人和人之间相互理解，是非常困难的一件事。经历、职业、阶层、趣味相同或者相近，只是增加相互了解的可能，却不是充分条件，就像关在同一栏里的猪，再多的相似又能怎么样？我不相信猪和猪之间，有相互理解的智慧。  理解的前提是有独立的思考，群氓对教主的理解，越自以为深刻...

                    <a class="pl" href="https://book.douban.com/review/1040880/#comments">(7回应)</a>
